# Project Structure Guidelines

## Directory Organization
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router
│   ├── api/               # API routes
│   ├── (auth)/           # Auth route group
│   ├── (marketing)/      # Marketing pages
│   └── (dashboard)/      # Dashboard pages
├── components/            # Shared UI components
│   ├── ui/              # Base UI components
│   ├── forms/           # Form components
│   └── layouts/         # Layout components
├── screens/              # Feature-specific views
│   └── [feature]/
│       ├── [Feature]View.tsx
│       ├── components/   # Feature components
│       ├── sections/    # Page sections
│       └── hooks/       # Feature hooks
├── actions/             # Server actions
├── services/            # External services
├── hooks/               # Custom React hooks
├── utils/               # Utility functions
├── lib/                 # Third-party configs
├── interfaces/          # TypeScript interfaces
├── types/               # TypeScript types
├── constants/           # App constants
├── config/              # App configuration
├── mocks/              # Mock data
└── styles/             # Global styles
```

## File Naming Conventions
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utilities: `camelCase.ts`
- Hooks: `use[HookName].ts`
- Constants: `CONSTANT_NAME.ts` or `constants.ts`
- Types/Interfaces: `IEntityName.ts` or `types.ts`
- Tests: `[name].test.ts` or `[name].spec.ts`

## Import Rules
- Use absolute imports with @/ alias
- Group imports by category
- Order: React/Next → Third-party → Internal → Relative

## Component Organization
- One component per file
- Co-locate related files (styles, tests, types)
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Extract complex logic to custom hooks

## Feature Organization
Each feature should have:
- View component (container)
- Section components (layout)
- UI components (presentation)
- Actions (data operations)
- Types (TypeScript definitions)
- Tests (unit and integration)

## Code Colocation
Keep related code together:
- Component + styles + tests
- Feature + actions + types
- Utils + tests

## Barrel Exports
Use index.ts for clean imports:
```typescript
// components/index.ts
export { Button } from "./Button";
export { Card } from "./Card";
export { Input } from "./Input";
```